flawed_nl_solution:
Susie earned $10 x 3 = $<<10*3=30>>30 per day.
Last week, she earned a total of $30 x 7 = $<<30*7=120>>120.
She spent $120 x 3/10 = $<<120*3/10=36>>36 on make-up.
While she spent $120 x 2/5 = $<<120*2/5=48>>48 on her skincare products.
Thus, she spent a total of $36 + $48 = $<<36+48=84>>84 from her earnings.
Therefore, Susie is left with $120 - $84 = $<<120-84=36>>36 from her earnings last week.
#### 36
